                            <span class="hotel-card_subtitle">MONUMENT</span>
                            <h3 class="css_heading">  RED FORT </h3>
                            <p class="hotel-card_text content-justify">
                                The Red Fort Complex was built as the palace fort of Shahjahanabad – the new capital of the fifth Mughal Emperor of India,
                                Shah Jahan. Named for its massive enclosing walls of red sandstone, it is adjacent to an older fort, the Salimgarh, built by
                                Islam Shah Suri in 1546, with which it forms the Red Fort Complex.An earlier red fort had been built in Old Delhi in the 11th
                                century by the Tomara king Anangapala.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="hotel-box-wrapper style4">
                        <div class="hotel-image style4">
