                            <h4 class="css_heading"> LOTUS TEMPLE</h4>
                            <p class="hotel-card_text mr-n1 content-justify">
                                East of Nehru place, this temple is built in the shape of a lotus flower and is the last of seven Major Bahai's
                                temples built around the world. Completed in1986 it is set among the lush green landscaped gardens.
                                Lotus Temple, Bahāʾī Faith house of worship, or mashriq al-adhkār (Arabic: “a place where the uttering of the name
                                of God arises at dawn”), in New Delhi.
                                In the early 21st century it was one of only nine mashriqs in the world.
                            </p>

